                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13582: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-29T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 29, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 29—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1049. My 1043, noon, today. A Japanese officer called on Colonel Price today and
                    explained that the violations were due to a recent change in personnel. He
                    promised that effective steps to prevent passage of Japanese men under arms
                    through the American defense sector will be taken at once.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow, Peiping and Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
